Well - yes - well a sanitary placer, it's such as - lavatories, washbasins and all that, used to have to place 'em in a sagger and carry 'em up what they called then the horse, in a bottle necked kiln - oven we used to call 'em and - that was sanitary pla
cing, used to have to go with that on his head up a ladder because - we call it the horse of course because it had got - you know household steps that have got like a platform on the top, well this was a platform on the top but it was shaped the shape of 
a sagger so it wouldn't slip on the top you see, and otherwise it was just what we called horse and - steps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Can you explain what a sagger is?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
