Well - no, he didn't have any - part time jobs to my knowledge. Only occasionally if he happened t
o be - they used to be short of work or anything of that, there used to be what they call boat emptying on the canal, and if he wasn't working then he used to go boat emptying 'til - next day he was work you know, and - odd jobs at sagger - placing. You s
e
e, if they weren't working, say they were on four days a week, he'd go and stand at top of the town 'til he saw somebody come and it's what they called drawing, that's drawing saggers out of a red hot oven when it had been fired, you see, and he used to g
o do a days draw - what they called drawing.
\par 
