No, it was when the - pit strikes were on you see, and he had to - we'd no coal or anything and he'd got to earn a bit some way with a big family like that and he used to go out and me mother and - per
haps one or two of us used to go to the soup kitchen and take a jug at dinnertimes you know, this what we've had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 What were soup kitchens then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Well - it was a man - how can I tell you. It was different soup kitchens were set up in differe
nt areas you see while the strike was on, and - this man that did this they used to boil such as offal and all that, the butchers, you see. Well he'd got a big boiler, well he used to make it - make soup in that boiler you know and - used to get - differe
nt things you know purpose to help - those that were on strike.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 This would be while you were still at school would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
This was while I was still at school. Well - while the war was on - no, I wasn't at school when this strike was on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 The 1926 strike?
