Yes. And - I was working then and I was working at Tealings at the time and I used to work four days a week and those days I didn't I used to have to go - I used to go and fetch the coals from me father and we used to sell it to different
 ones round about as hadn't got any. And I used to go from work - without any tea or anything, we used to go from work to Snede Colliery, which is a mile and a half to two mile from where I worked, and used to carry a bag of coal down from there to my hom
e
 again Longport Station, that's where it was and - then me mother'd have me tea ready, it'd be waiting you know for - have me tea ready for when I come home. And - if me father - when I got up there I saw that me father had got a bit too much for him then
 I would go back after I'd had me tea and fetch it. Help to fetch it anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 That was on top of a days work?
