same as myself, I don't know how ever my mother did manage. I don't honestly. And if anyone asks me now how I carried on while my husband was an invalid, thirty-one years, and me a cripple and going to work, I couldn't tell them. Honestly I could not tell
 
'em. Like my mother I didn't even throw potato water away. We used that as stock. Cabbage water or anything, and - as regards myself I used mince - mince vegetables and everything, me mother had never got a mincer but - I've known times when we've had an 
e
gg between two. Definite - definite we know what poverty is. And you can understand me when I say I've had no proper training for anything, until after I was married. I can honestly say - until I was - been married - two years, I never knew what it was fo
