 a cardigan or anything of that. Never. I knit me first own cardigan - I've always done a lot of knitting, I used to knit at school, and I used to do a lot of the turning of the heels of stockings. And I remember me father got his hair off one day, and he
 
says, look, if you bring anymore of them they'll go back of the fire whether you like it or not. I don't care what the teacher says, you must not bring any more of them. I used to sit there all night, you know, 'til about - ten o'clock and when mother and
 
dad used to go out anywhere I used to definitely bring them, and I hid them in the house so me dad wouldn't see them. Purpose to do it at school. And I remember one day - I know I'd been - you can't see - you can see it now - can you see that seal there? 
