now that man's got two children? And he - it looks like Mr Joseph will have to take him home. He says, but - I'm afraid I shall have to take you in to Mr Joe. I said, you can please yourself. I said, but listen here, I said, if I go into the office to Mr 
J
oseph I shall ask Mr Joseph for a private interview, because, I said, I shall get flogged and I shall repeat what that man said to me. I said, I was carrying out, as normal, I said, same as he was carrying to the warehouse, I said, and he came out with a 
c
ertain - certain thing to me. And he says, well - what did he say? I said, that's my business. I said, he's suffering for what he said. I said, and if he's got two children, I said, do you know he's got a son - his eldest son is the church organist - and 
h
im coming out with words like that. And he tried me very hard. But they never took me in the office and he never known what he said. And they've never known the word. I daren't go home and tell 'em I was in a bother, 'cos I should get thrashed because I s
h
ould have to repeat it, you see. How my parents were that strict, although - if I'd have gone in to Mr Joseph, I would have had to tell my mother and father that I was in trouble and what would happen you know, I might get sacked for it 'cos I hit a man. 
A
nd - 'course when me parents asked me what I said I - I said to 'em you'll only give me a good hiding if I tell you. So me father says to me, I will not. - thrash you. So of course - nobody else - I had the house cleared of me brothers and sisters were ou
t
 and at that time we only lived in a one bedroom - one - room, there was a room and then a little pantry here, and in the pantry there was shelves on that side - this end were coal under the stairs, and - there was a bucket with a box on as we used to hav
e to wash in, all in the pantry, because there was only like this room and this little }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1310893\charrsid9981595 pantry}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 . And there was two bedrooms upstairs which was halved - kind of - this style, the two bedrooms were made like that you see. Well here was a bedroom. This was - one
 bed - this is where, when I got married, I had that one bedroom and I lived with me mother. Of course the others - some of the others were - and - me mother used to - put - no, it would be a bit bigger than that - me mother used to part this room like th
at, me mum and dad had that room, lads in there and the girls in there. And that's how she split her house up. So you can see what - and the rent then at that house was three shilling a week. Look at it today. There is a fantastic difference.
