Well she used to take washing in. Yes. She took washing in. And I remember I used to have to come home and do the ironing. There was a person name of S
pencer, they used to - skin rabbits and etcetera you know so there would be the rabbit aprons and overalls, I used to have to iron 'em when I come back whether eit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid345849\charrsid9981595 her}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595  at work or - or at school partly. The washing as her used to do, I used to have a to have
 a job doing the ironing, we always had a job, always. A job each, and I don't think it did any harm. Even - cleaning shoes for - different ones. I - I think - well we used to clean shoes for coppers. We used to do six pair of shoes for a penny. Six pair 
of shoes - what would they think now, they'd say - oh, clean mine, clean mine. But a penny then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 You'd clean the family's shoes?
