et some friends and he'd had a drink of beer and he come in acting you know, he was a - terror for that, he was only a little man like this, and - he came one day in acting as though he was drunk. Oh, I said, our dad, have you been drinking? You know, qui
te upset about it. I said, Miss Wright'll be here just now. And - you know - are you all right? Who's Miss Wright? And - anyway he carried on for a bit. I said, oh come on, and I picket him up and he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid816496\charrsid9981595 doesn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595  move. And I took him bed. Carried him upstairs. A
nd as soon as I'd dropped him on the bed he said, Elsie, never do that again. I said, well never you do that again father. I said, never you kind me up like that that you're drunk. You see, I picked him up because I was bigger boned and that, me father on
