, but this is the story how - Doctor Stevensons home was first - he rented a house and this was the first beginning of Doctor Stevenson's homes and he rented this house and put someone in it to look after these boys, and they had a home to 
sleep, with beds and everything you see. This story was told to us, read to us, a true story and - in Sunday school when - this first effort started of collecting for the homes in envelopes well I went - they went from door to door and at one time I could
 tell you every house and every street in Longport and how many houses there was in a street. And we used to put a - envelope in every house and then go back again and - collect them on the Saturday. This was on the same days as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13589634\charrsid9981595 Daisy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595  Day, when all this mon
ey had to be in. And I can remember one thing in particular, going to Doctor Motts, and I went in the surgery way and he took me up by the scruff to the neck, I'll never forget it, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13589634\charrsid9981595 cached}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595  hold of back of neck, back way for this, you know, very stern, and -
 that is the only time that I got any - rebuke I must say for - collecting, I never got insulted or told to banner off or anything of this, I always went with the same words, I've call for Doctor Stevensons Home and Orphanage envelope please. And that was
 
the way we always had to address and - I always went with the civility as I was learnt and I always got the civility. I either got an empty envelope or penny in it or something of that. And - then in the afternoon, we collected like Thursday, Friday and S
a
turday, fetched them in, and at the Saturday afternoon I used to go on the same square as I told you about breaking the lamp there, and we used to have a stall selling daisies and - used to have a box. And of course it was quite close to the station and q
u
ite close to the trams. Well we used to have some - one or two that - for the trams, collecting, and one or two down at the station as they came off the station. And this we used to do very well. We used to - always tried to get most of course, in us boxe
s
 and - Mr Ball, he was the secretary at the time, he always used to tell everyone separately how much they'd got in their box and this - was mostly how - during July, some time in June and July, but otherwise Saturday afternoons we used to go out play on 
the square you know and - but I always - did this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 What would happen on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Well - the usual routine. Breakfast and - off to Sunday school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Where would the Sunday school be? Was this chapel or church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Chapel, Wesleyan chapel. We'
d - it was not very far from home and we uses to go to Sunday school first, from Sunday school into church you see, we'd have to go into church afterwards, and - if such as me - me mother was - say looking after this lady as had had a baby, I - I would pe
rhaps be allowed to come out of Sunday school and not go into church, go home and help my mother getting Sunday dinner. But mostly - more }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13589634\charrsid9981595 oftener}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595  than not we had to go straight into church. We went church Sunday afternoon, dad took us after we'd come out of
 church a walk which probably meant we were - didn't get back home, he used to take us round Bradwell Wood and; Port Hill and places like that, walking, not riding, walking. And - we'd perhaps go picking bluebells and - in the woods. Different places - we
l
l me mother would probably be having a rest Sunday afternoon, me dad had taken us out and - she'd perhaps read or something of that while Dad had got us out. And then she would have us tea ready for when we came back. And then it was - teatime, we'd have 
t
ea, we'd have little extras, it wouldn't be extras to a lot of people, but we'd perhaps have a tin of salmon between us - and - then I'd go - the older ones would go back to church Sunday night. Come home - which would be about half past seven or quarter 
to eight we would all be allowed to go on us own - a walk or anywhere, providing you were in by nine o'clock. That was us time. And - when I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13589634\charrsid9981595 teenagers}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595  we had to be in by quarter to ten to fetch me father's half pint, night time. He wouldn't go out but he always had half pint in the house at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Your Sundays were pretty full weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Your mother made an effort for anniversaries to get you different clothes?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Would you usually have different clothes for Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Well - we used to keep these as we had for the anniversary until - 'til they were worn out you know absolutely for Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Would your mum and dad think it wrong for you to play games on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Well - certain games, yes - say football or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 So you were expected to be quieter on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
To behave on Sundays, yes. Such as football they wouldn't allow - but sitting and play snakes and ladders or dominoes, a quiet game, you could stay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Did your parents attend a place of worship or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Not much. Funerals, marriages and deaths and that's about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Your father wouldn't go with the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
No. No, we went on us own. But - me mother used to go - to a Fellowship one day in the week you know, as her night out we used 
to call that you know. Oh it's mother's night out, I can't come out tonight you know. I'd got to look after twins and me mother'd go to Fellowship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Would you say your parents were Wesleyans as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Yes. Definitely, me father's father was a local preacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Yes. That were - Sunday school treats we used to call them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 You told me about the trips on the canal, were there other places you went to?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Malcrop. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 What other social activiti
es organised by the chapel did you take part in, did you have Band of Hope or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Yes. Band of Hope, and there was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Would you go to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Missionary - yes - missionary concert with - which - our anniversary clothes mostly did you know
, the clothing for it, but if we had any - other clothes to find - they were made up in paper and - you know - different things - dresses like this, when we used to put the missionary shows on - it was mostly singing but - on the stage, what we had for th
e
 anniversary, in the church. It was round - the stage was made round the pulpit and we used to do these things on the stage. Dressed up as Indians and - different - nationalities of clothing you know we used to have, and this time it used to - be - the co
l
lection was for missionary funds. And yet - I couldn't say that we were - religious minded or anything of this and - although I tell you these things about the church it wasn't that - I got religious - upbringings or anything of this in the home, you know
, it - it was just activities as - whatever was on we took part in it. As regards that - practice time, you see that was an high time for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Was there a chapel choir?
