\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 No. Only what we went Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Music Halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 No, didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Well after I was left school this would be. And I us
ed to stand market for - Mr Kearns, fruit man, and - here again I think I was a bit - what shall - how shall I put it, I can't exactly explain how now - I was a bit - trying to have me own way, 'cos I was left school and - I said to me mother - mother, ca
n
 I - it'll be late when I come in tonight. And she would say - she said, why, where are you going? Of course I said, I'm going to the pictures, see a picture. I said, it's only the last picture. I said, I've got meet Lizzie. That was the other girl like, 
w
e were going pictures, after I'd finished the market. Don't forget be in by ten o'clock then. You can go tonight but be in for ten o'clock. And this is where I think I began to put a firm stamp for myself, as regards this. I was earning the money and I wa
s
 going to enjoy the money that - I had - I thought to me own mind you know. And of course I used to stand about eight hours at the market, Friday and Saturday. So - I was beginning to think I ought to have a bit of pleasure in life I suppose then. Was onl
y thirteen but - this was it. I - I was allowed to go pictures on Saturday night, but I had to pay for myself, and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 But while you were at school this wasn't on at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Oh no. There was a picture palace as we used to go and pay tuppence for - Sa
turday mornings, you know, that - all of us went as regards that while me mother got done. Then everything'd be done up so that she could start shopping after dinner you see. We used to go to the pictures in Longport which - there again was only like goin
g to the bottom of this street. So - that was allowed, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 You would do that most Saturdays would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Most Saturdays, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Penny a week. Earned a bit, then we didn't have us penny, we had w
hat we'd earned ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 What would you spend the penny on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Perhaps extra sweets I would think myself, I just forget how we would spend - but because me mum used to give us a toffee each every morning. But then we went to the - when we went to
 the shops - did the shopping for us mother - it wasn't far, only across a main road for us - we used to go across the shop and then on a Friday or Saturday we used to take - me mother or one of us'd go across and pay the bill. Even if me mother went to p
ay they always used to give her a bag of sweets, a big bagful of sweets. Well we used to say, ain't there no shop drop this week. You know, if we just hadn't had one whenever we knew she'd been the shop, no }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13589634\charrsid9981595 shop drop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595  this week? And this used to be - said, y
ou know, and we used to have it in the week along with what me mother used to dish out to us, one a week - one a morning when we went school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after the house or the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Well no, I don't think
 so - not - she used to have a - now then, welfare nurse I think. Her used to come occasionally and - to see if the children were all right you know, under fives - or under threes it was then. Same as when the twins were little, you got a welfare nurse - 
you know, to come and just ask questions about it, if your mother didn't take 'em the clinic, but more often than not my mother took 'em clinic so we could have cheap milk.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Well we mo
re or less - we - used to help and - and you see as a confinement she'd have a nurse and then - us children'd have to help. Me mother's sister might come like whole we were very very young, I can't just remember her or anything but - I think her sisters'd
 probably come and see to me mother, you know, but normally - as far back as I can remember either me father looked after her or - us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Did your dad take time off work to do it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 No. No. No, he - without it were when she was - the day she was 
having the baby or something of that, he would the running up and down for the nurse and all that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Oh yes. Brothers and sisters of me mother's and - me father's relatives lived about ha
lf a mile away from home. We used to go, you know, different ones - I don't think for a minute but what one of me father's sisters or something got that hadn't used to look to me mother when the - with such as me and that, I don't remember - remember anyt
hing there but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 But the children weren't packed off into a childrens home or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Oh nothing - nothing of that, never have done. They've always coped, yes. Perhaps a neighbour'd come in you know when - and help that day or that time while t
he midwife was there and that, done the - get the hot water and all that, she'd probably do that you know, everything - knew where everything was. But me - mother as regards confinement, when - we was expecting the babe - you know when she started she - i
n
 labour - she would start and she'd put all her things on the clothes maid, they'd all be ready aired, they'd all be there for the midwife. - Brown paper and everything for the bed, they used to use a lot of brown paper and - used to go - the of course th
e
 midwife used to burn it on the fire and - when it was done with, just have it for - instead of marking the beds and things like this - but - I don't ever remember anybody coming without it is like - same as me mother's sister or one of the neighbours com
ing in just at the time she was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 How often did relatives used to come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Oh - oh they very often used to come, either one or another, with - me mother'd got three sisters and one brother. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13589634\charrsid9981595 Ca}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 n't just say how many me father got, I think he'd got abo
ut four brothers and two sisters. But they used to come different times, you know, occasionally come, perhaps once a month or something of that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Me mother had a friend - that she'd been - to in a confinement, she 
was good to her when she was confined you know once, and - she kept her friendship up for - quite a while. But - how she knew this woman was - through service, when she was a teenager me mother'd - been in service you see and she'd been in service with a 
p
erson - that this one of her relatives you know and they'd - said like - as me mother would be a good friend to her when she happened to come to live down there you see. And she kept - in fact - some of us - older ones used to say, oh her thinks more abou
t Lizzie }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13589634\charrsid9981595 Rowling\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
 than her thinks of us, you know. Since we've been married you know and - but this was the case of course, this one close friends, this - she'd got -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Did your dad have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 We - he never seemed to - he'd got a lot of friends
, me father had, everybody was - but not a friend - friend as he went out with, made a habit of going out with. Me mother didn't make a friend of Mrs Rolley to that extent. But - they always - she always seemed to be popping in, you know, she didn't go ou
t with her or anything of that. Me father would make friends easily, you know, but - not to go out with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
So when your mother saw Mrs Rolley, Mrs Rolley would come to your house or your mother would go to hers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 They wouldn't be going out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 No, they wouldn't go out together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Were there any friends that your mum and dad had in common?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Well they were both - Mrs Rolley was friends with both and her husband you know. With mum and dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 If people came into the house would th
ey be offered something to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Oh always. You never - it was said, it didn't matter who comes in you know there's a cup of tea and everything got you know before -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 But people would come in casually rather than being given a set invitation?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Did neighbours come in and out as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Oh they would come in just the same you know and - always a knock on the door first you know, it was a - door was always open kind of style to anybody. Me father always used to 
say, well, my door'swings on hinges. If you want me we're there and if you want any help }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13589634\charrsid9981595 we\rquote re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595  there to help you you know - but otherwise - he wouldn't sit in anyone's house, and he wouldn't encourage 'em a lot, you know, to - he was more home, you know, his own home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 He }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13589634\charrsid9981595 preferred}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595  people to come to his house rather than him go to theirs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Yes. If they wanted him for anything he would prefer 'em come to his house. Although, the same as I say, it was a poor home, but it was clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Yes. They do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
