\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13589634\charrsid9981595 d to cut the prints for transfe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
rers you see. Used to call 'em a cutter. And I worked - three weeks as I told you before not so long ago, only worked about three weeks and then the holidays come. And - but I 
wouldn't have been able to gone to work if I had. I had - it would be the tar that they used I think - but I had something wrong with me arms, me elbows and everything, and the doctor called it the Scotch itch. But I was all broke out and everything, so o
f
 course this is where me parents wouldn't let me go back to the job because - it was - must have been that as caused it, otherwise - I was - ill at home ten week with that. So - of course - the job - I could - with me hands and that all being broke out I 
couldn't touch anything, you know, I couldn't do anything - normally that - only feed myself, in fear - in fright of getting - septic or anything of that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 So you worked three week and you had ten weeks off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Yes.
