d over to your mum would go into the general family expenditure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Yes. Expenditure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
How did you get on with the people you worked with, did you find it a big step to move from school into work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Oh no, I don't think I did because at this thr
ee week was a break you know, a breaking in, then having ten week at home through this - Scotch itch as the doctors call it and - I seemed to think - because there were some of my schoolfriends really in the warehouse the same you know as went in - one or
 
two of them - they were probably a bit better advanced than me because they'd started straight from school. And I'd gone this thirteen week without - knowing as much as them you know quite. They were used to it when I started there although they were very
 helpful with me you know, they helped me in a lot of ways, even schoolfriends there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 You spent fifteen to eighteen months in this place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Where did you go after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 I went to Saddlers - mould running. This is the first I had to 
mould running - in clay state this was, the first time I'd done anything of the sort. Here again - I worked - with a woman that was the maker you know. And - that was it. As regards - I just - running the moulds in and out of stove you know with her and -
 
I got on all right with her, she was a lady - that had come - quite close to us and I got on all right with her, but I still only worked a short time there. And then I went to a job that I'd always wanted to do, although I didn't think it was this hard, I
 
went running for flat. You see it was teapot covers while I was in the red clay and I went in to work with me cousin. We were great friends - and she was working in the falt shop same time so I went work with her, with another maker. - And we did - I did 
very well there, I was soon - promoted and made tower you know and - from towing I went making and - I worked there until I was married.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 What does towing mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Well towing is taking; making smooth edges on plates. Used to use a cutting tin at th
e time, but now I believe they don't use a cutting tin they used just - we used to have to use sandpaper then and - like a kind of a hair, it's some similar to cotton wool only - they - used to wipe it over with that so they wouldn't leave any dust on. Th
is again was - we used to have to blow a lot, a lot of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13589634\charrsid9981595 dusty}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
 work you know, you used to have to blow the dust off and - what the fan didn't take you blew off - up the fan and then - 'course they had to go into the places for firing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 This again was a five and a half day week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 But your wages were up from the three and six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Yes. A little bit. You did a hundred dozen of flat for three and fourpence. And a hundred dozen not at twelve to the dozen nor thirteen. Twenty four, it's jus
t according to the size. Twenty-four to the dozen, twenty-eight to the dozen. Thirty to the dozen, thirty six to the dozen, up to forty-eight, each sis. You see, if you were one small work then you got to get more through your fingers for the price. And w
e used to get -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 This was kind of piecework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Yes. Three and fourpence of a hundred dozen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 How many dozen could you do in a day then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Well - it was jolly hard work to do seventy-five. Seventy-five to a hundred, good days work with no carrying out or anything but you had to carry out - carry your work out to the placers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 So the most you could earn was three and four a day if you were lucky?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 At this time were you still having to hand your money over to your mother?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Yes. Yes. Oh yes, I turned all up to her 'til I was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 But you got a bit more pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Penny in the shilling. Just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 But this was a job you enjoyed even though it was such hard work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Yes. Yes. I enjoyed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 You kept this job until you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Until I got married, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Did you work after you were married at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Oh yes, I've had - I've had to work, I've an invalid husband.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Were these jobs in the pots as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Some of them, yes. 
Ammunitions and - Mechelin Tyre Company, I went in there, I started as a clean - as a - a sweeper in the shops and worked meself up to a - what it - maker you know of tyres and working there. Any particular job you want describing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Was there any job you think you would have liked to have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Well - as regards that I would have liked to have gone to Mechelin kind of first and - and learned the trade properly from the beginning you know and worked myself up as - as it was I just came - kind of wo
rked myself up to - about four jobs higher, and I worked there - three years and a half you see, so I did get a - a big higher wages, I wasn't always a sweeper. I worked in the semi-cuver which is a private room, but - no one was allowed in only those as 
worked in it you see. But - this is as I say, I would have liked to have learned more about it but of course - I had been on other jobs and been a maker by trade which I liked but it was a dirty job and this is it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Did any of the jobs you had have an a
pprenticeship or training period attached to them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Yes. Oh yes, there was seven years apprenticeship to - making. But I got making - after towing you know, I went making and - of course the war came on and - this is how - I gave over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Did you belong to any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
I belonged to the potters union while I was in the pots and - the Transport and General Workers union while I was at Redway Green, Muniotions and - 'course after that, I didn't - I was in the Transport when I was at Michelin
 as well. But after that I hadn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Why did you join the unions, because it was expected of you because you worked there or did you strongly feel that trade unions offered something to workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 No - I - I think if a job's worth fighting for, same
 as the unions fight for 'em then it's up to you to help to support 'em. Not that I understand anything as they were you know at the present moment, only - same as - when you got hurt or anything of that you know - compensation cases and that - although I
 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13589634\charrsid9981595 ignored}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
 them that's where I had me first accident on potbank and that was me knee which has been broke many and many and many a time since and me legs you know, but - I was on compensation and started back mould running - and went for less money than I was
 getting compensation. So this was - 'course that was with me mother saying like as - what time I was back work and that although the doctor said he wouldn't bad responsible when I went up and wouldn't be responsible if I started work but me mother was al
ways on, I was - ought to have been back work 'cos I was walking about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Between sixteen and seventeen then, you know, and - 'course I'd already had me knee out of place but I'd - that case -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 What did you do to your knee, how did it happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Well taking the moulds and the what sit when I had this compensation, I - I was a moulder and that for dishes and - I was going up to take them and as I turned round on a top of a steps I fell and of course I put me knee out at 
the time and - the maker let - another - another maker let his daughter bring me home and - of course I was at home quite a - while, nearly six month with it and of course - it was; beginning to make me mother feel that I wasn't trying to get it right you
 know. But this was it, I'd gone against the doctor's orders and went - running moulds again for less money. Purpose to get in this shop where me cousin was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
At this time did you feel that the employers and the workers had the same interests or different?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 In which way do you mean this, I mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Did you feel the employers weren't all that bothered about their workers as long as they got the right amount of stuff out at the end of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Well really, yes, I - so long as the work was - r
ight and they were more interested in as much as they could get you know out of a worker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 You didn't feel there was any body terribly interested in you as a person?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 As a person, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Did you feel there were any divisions of interest among th
e workers themselves, some people say in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers, did you feel that or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
No, because I don't think there was anything - - the same you know as regards craftsmen and that, I think everybody was like me, they were doing the work at their first job and stepping up to the next, most of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 With the pots all the jobs are so interdependent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Everybody's got to pull their weight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Pull their weight, yes. T
o get the finished product and - same as - and bonus - you see, when I was making - if a tower didn't do the amount of work you got to ask another tower do it, you see, give her work to - and this you see would mean that all your shelves and everything we
r
e blocked up and if you were to get any wages, same as at this time I'd got an invalid husband, and I were only married nine month when - my husband was certified - and this is - I was anxious to get more money, but I couldn't get it if I didn't have - an
d if you had a good tower you come to her, you'd give her a little extra and - if she was going to work hard with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Well - yes, I would but - still it - I alwa
ys thought it was a matter of progress you know, a better job kind of style, you had - more money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 You continued to live at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Did starting full time work change your relationship with you parents at all?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Well - no, it didn't do - yes, expected to do same. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 You were expected to behave like their child and keep the rules of the house?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Of the house and everything - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 Did your brothers and sisters treat you in any different way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2889289 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
No. Oh no, no definitely no, because - I remember one instance. You see I got another sister working and I was doing upstairs one day and my sister had bought herself a jumper. She'd got it on a hanger behind the door and I remember I was doing upstai
rs and this jumper - well - a coat, there was a hook on the door and the coat - the jumper was under the coat, and - I was doing - dusting round the what sit and everything and I must have touched this coat, must have touched it because it fell. And what 
i
t did, it fell - on this jumper, the neck of the jumper, ripped it in two. 'Course - oh she went shy high when she come home. She - fly at me and of course after we - had a bit of a barney at home as regards of this - me father and me mother, I've had eno
u
gh of that, it was an accident, you know. But it wasn't finished there. We used to go and argue in bed when we'd gone to bed you know and - and - I had to save my pocket money, buy her another. But she machined it up as it could be used of course, which w
e
 were always brought up that way. But - I bought this other, well - she went and bought it and - paid for it what her wanted you know out of my money and - 'cos I had used to save as such as I could and - when she come she wouldn't even let me have the on
e
 that had got ripped so - this was it. She liked that as well you see so she wouldn't pat with it. But it - I'd got to pay for another one. 'Cos parents - me parents wouldn't let - her keep falling out with me, it was just that we slept together and me an
d her - fell out in the bedroom as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid469682 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11499485\charrsid9981595 
