she was a person like me, she'd - been brought up rough, you know, and - she couldn't always have new clothes here I didn't have new clothes. And I remember once - as - my - I had a frock, well me - me mother had it given to her and I had a costume, I thi
n
k I told that on the other tape, well this is - I remember now that she was so stiff and I was just the opposite, you know, so slim that - she used to cry because she used to think that my clothes fitted me better, well it was only the coat, the frock, an
y
thing that fitted this girl you know fitted me and the coat and had was made by a relative of this girl and - of course I was quite tidy, to tell you the truth this costume I had was when I was seventeen, and - I got married in it. I only had - I left hom
